{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:31:40.225146+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:z12qZb | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 5a8674ab028bc77e93f4d81bf13aa2ecfaec4061)", "id": "lc_65244a02-8e23-45c6-82d9-84521e9a0072"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:z12qZb | # TensorFlow is much easier to install using Anaconda, especially\n| MCP:z12qZb | # on Windows or when using a GPU. Please see the installation\n| MCP:z12qZb | # instructions in INSTALL.md\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Core scientific packages\n| MCP:z12qZb | jupyterlab~=4.0.8\n| MCP:z12qZb | matplotlib~=3.8.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | numpy~=1.26.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | pandas~=2.1.3\n| MCP:z12qZb | scipy~=1.11.3\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Machine Learning packages\n| MCP:z12qZb | scikit-learn~=1.3.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: the XGBoost library is only used in chapter 7\n| MCP:z12qZb | xgboost~=2.0.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: the transformers library is only used in chapter 16\n| MCP:z12qZb | transformers~=4.35.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### TensorFlow-related packages\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # If you have a TF-compatible GPU and you want to enable GPU support, then\n| MCP:z12qZb | # replace tensorflow-serving-api with tensorflow-serving-api-gpu.\n| MCP:z12qZb | # Your GPU must have CUDA Compute Capability 3.5 or higher support, and\n| MCP:z12qZb | # you must install CUDA, cuDNN and more: see tensorflow.org for the detailed\n| MCP:z12qZb | # installation instructions.\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorflow~=2.14.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: the TF Serving API library is just needed for chapter 18.\n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorflow-serving-api~=2.14.0  # or tensorflow-serving-api-gpu if gpu\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorboard~=2.14.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorboard-plugin-profile~=2.14.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorflow-datasets~=4.9.3\n| MCP:z12qZb | tensorflow-hub~=0.15.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Used in chapter 10 and 19 for hyperparameter tuning\n| MCP:z12qZb | keras-tuner~=1.4.6\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Reinforcement Learning library (chapter 18)\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # There are a few dependencies you need to install first, check out:\n| MCP:z12qZb | # https://github.com/Farama-Foundation/Gymnasium\n| MCP:z12qZb | swig~=4.1.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | gymnasium[Box2D,atari,accept-rom-license]~=0.29.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | # WARNING: on Windows, installing Box2D this way requires:\n| MCP:z12qZb | # * Swig: http://www.swig.org/download.html\n| MCP:z12qZb | # * Microsoft C++ Build Tools:\n| MCP:z12qZb | #   https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/visual-cpp-build-tools/\n| MCP:z12qZb | # It's much easier to use Anaconda instead.\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Image manipulation\n| MCP:z12qZb | Pillow~=10.1.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | graphviz~=0.20.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Google Cloud Platform - used only in chapter 19\n| MCP:z12qZb | google-cloud-aiplatform~=1.36.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | google-cloud-storage~=2.13.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | ##### Additional utilities\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Efficient jobs (caching, parallelism, persistence)\n| MCP:z12qZb | joblib~=1.3.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Easy http requests\n| MCP:z12qZb | requests~=2.31.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Nice utility to diff Jupyter Notebooks.\n| MCP:z12qZb | nbdime~=3.2.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # May be useful with Pandas for complex \"where\" clauses (e.g., Pandas\n| MCP:z12qZb | # tutorial).\n| MCP:z12qZb | numexpr~=2.8.7\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: these libraries can be useful in chapter 3, exercise 4.\n| MCP:z12qZb | nltk~=3.8.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | urlextract~=1.8.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: tqdm displays nice progress bars, ipywidgets for tqdm's notebook\n| MCP:z12qZb | #           support\n| MCP:z12qZb | tqdm~=4.66.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | ipywidgets~=8.1.1\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: pydot is only used in chapter 10 for tf.keras.utils.plot_model()\n| MCP:z12qZb | pydot~=1.4.2\n| MCP:z12qZb | \n| MCP:z12qZb | # Optional: statsmodels is only used in chapter 15 for time series analysis\n| MCP:z12qZb | statsmodels~=0.14.0\n| MCP:z12qZb | ", "id": "lc_954220f3-e997-4b41-b58b-5214a872edba"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c283f4c2-03ca-403a-bdde-e3ffed3a9296", "tool_call_id": "call_ea14d58766d7412e8341c674", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
